td-efa10b: Escape or reject pipe delimiters in canonical payload fields
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, security

Description:
GA.Audit.Chain builds payloads with raw to_string values and joins on '|', so values containing '|' create ambiguous encodings and can preserve the same payload across different field splits (app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:65, app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:92). This breaks canonical unambiguity and can undermine tamper evidence. Found by: Code Quality, Security, Codex Fresh Eyes (manual equivalent).

Acceptance Criteria:
Canonical payload generation must either escape delimiters per field or reject input containing '|'. Add tests showing two different attribute maps with embedded delimiters cannot produce identical payload/checksum, and existing behavior remains deterministic for normal inputs.

