td-dac713: Validate key and checksum inputs before chain operations
Status: [in_progress]
Type: task | Priority: P2
Labels: review-finding, code-quality

Description:
compute_checksum/3 and canonical_payload/2 rely on specs but do not enforce key/checksum shape at runtime; malformed previous_checksum values can raise during payload join and weak/empty keys are accepted silently (app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:27, app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:55, app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:62). Add explicit validation/guards and clear errors for invalid inputs. Found by: Code Quality, Security.

Acceptance Criteria:
Reject invalid inputs with deterministic behavior: key must be non-empty binary (or explicit 32-byte policy), previous_checksum must be nil or a checksum-shaped binary, and malformed inputs do not crash unexpectedly. Add unit tests for invalid key and previous_checksum cases.

